<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 4:24AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Areas of dense fog this morning...
Widespread fog, including areas of dense fog with visibilities
half mile or less, has developed overnight across southeastern
Michigan. Fog is expected to persist through the morning commute
before gradually dissipating mid to late morning. Motorists should
exercise caution when traveling this morning and be prepared for
rapidly changing visibilities.</description>
